Despite being the zone of the National Chairman of the ruling APC, Abdullahi Adamu, the party lost the Nasarawa West senatorial seat in the National Assembly elections held on Saturday. The Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) has declared Ahmed Wadada of the Social Democratic Party (SDP) as the winner of the Nasarawa West senatorial District election.  Despite being the zone of the National Chairman of the ruling APC, Abdullahi Adamu, the party lost the Nasarawa West senatorial seat in the National Assembly elections held on Saturday. The APC candidate, Shehu Tukur, was not listed by the Independent National Electoral Commission to contest for the Senate seat due to litigation issues.  The INEC returning agent for Nasarawa West Senatorial District, Prof Nasiruddeen Baba said the SDPâ€™s Wadada polled 96,488 votes while APC got 47,717 votes. The Peoples Democratic Party polled 46,820 and the Labour Party polled 33,228.  